SUMMARY:The Context Layer: The Emerging Stack for Context-Aware AI
DESCRIPTION:Data Science Raleigh\nAs enterprises push AI into production\, context isn’t a luxury—it’s a requirement. Whether you're mitigating hallucinations\, aligning responses with brand and policy guidelines\, or ensuring traceable\, compliant outcomes\, context-aware architecture is becoming foundational to trustworthy AI.\n\nThis webinar explores the “context layer”—the emerging stack of tools\, techniques\, and workflows that inject dynamic\, domain-specific intelligence into AI systems. We’ll examine how leading teams are designing for retrieval-augmented generation (RAG)\, grounding\, memory\, and orchestration to ensure outputs reflect the right data\, tone\, and constraints at the right time.\n\n**What You'll Learn:**\n\n1️⃣ **Architecting the Context Layer:** What the emerging stack looks like—from vector databases and memory systems to orchestration layers and policy enforcement.\n\n2️⃣ **Reducing Hallucinations:** How context-aware design helps constrain generative outputs to known\, verifiable sources.\n\n3️⃣ **Boosting Trust & Alignment:** Techniques for integrating domain-specific knowledge\, tone\, and compliance rules directly into AI interactions.\n\n4️⃣ **From Static to Dynamic Context:** When to use retrieval\, when to use memory\, and how to balance both for adaptive\, scalable systems.\n\n**[Register here](https://hubs.ly/Q042cLJx0)**
